snippet.textDisplay:
Hello TerminalMontage; I think as well as others that you qualify to a degree as genius. It's peculiar that those who are not genii, such as myself, may determine others to be so. I don't think you match the degree which those typically deemed genii are at -- Shakespeare, Mozart, Da Vinci, amongst others... I think there's a very good chance that in the work of those typically celebrated as genii supremely intelligent Aliens were involved, however, so I hesitate to be certain that their work is actually entirely of human hands -- in which case perhaps your work is in reality an example of the highest degree of excellence attainable by a human in artistic media (unless you are, wittingly or not, an abductee...). I love your videos; they're a great support to me in my chronic illness together with the games parodied and Arlo; I can't thank you enough.

I'm bold to present a little criticism here: perhaps there may be a way to reduce the intensity of the violence in your expression, a little, without compromising the quality of it -- I think the fantasy violence of Nintendo's core games is intense enough (Smash included); anything much more than that, including any degree of gore which is indulgent and not limited to medicine is a little strong for my taste (I imagine that I probably speak on behalf of a relatively small minority of your audience, however, in this regard; though one is as precious as a thousand, is it not). One could fairly argue that gore and violence are essential to conflict which is a core subject of art and so the depiction of which is necessary and creative; but I think there is fine line between indulgence and artistry in this regard -- in my own opinion, your work would improve if you were to attend a little to mastering further this balance (please forgive me if you are already currently working on this aspect). I oddly think however that the screams of the characters are done excellently -- they express eternal suffering and are very funny.

I want to say that I can feel for you that it must be extremely frustrating not to have the financial support behind you to support your work -- more frustrating than world six Yoshi's Island for 100 points even -- I really wish it were otherwise. You're not able to attend to your genius work as much as everyone who loves it, including yourself, would wish; anything less than the degree of production in your work that we all wish for is unhealthy and suppressed, I think we all feel. It's a pain and a shame and we your adoring audience feel that discomfort to a significant degree of that at which you must feel it. I hope I hope I hope for greater financial support for you to come.

I just watched both your Pikmin, Attack on Titian, and See You, Jelly Boy for the first time last night -- just genius -- thank you so much TerminalMontage. I can't choose a favourite from your videos, too many many of them -- Smash, Battle Royal, Mario, Breath, and on and on -- are too excellent.

With eternal gratitude and admiration,
Galen.
